content:
Creating a CSS animation that changes the size of an element multiple times can be achieved using keyframes to define the animation steps and applying this animation to the desired element. Here's a step-by-step guide along with an example:

1. **Define Keyframes**: Use the `@keyframes` rule to create an animation sequence. You can specify the percentage or keywords (`from`, `to`) to indicate points in the animation timeline.

2. **Apply Animation**: Use properties like `animation-name`, `animation-duration`, `animation-timing-function`, `animation-iteration-count`, and others to control the animation.

Here's an example of a CSS animation that changes the size of an element three times:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Size Change Animation</title>
    <style>
        /* Define the animation */
        @keyframes resize {
            0% {
                transform: scale(1);
            }
            25% {
                transform: scale(1.5);
            }
            50% {
                transform: scale(1);
            }
            75% {
                transform: scale(2);
            }
            100% {
                transform: scale(1);
            }
        }

        /* Apply the animation to the element */
        .animated-box {
            width: 100px;
            height: 100px;
            background-color: skyblue;
            animation-name: resize;
            animation-duration: 4s; /* Duration of the animation cycle */
            animation-timing-function: ease-in-out;
            animation-iteration-count: infinite; /* Repeat the animation indefinitely */
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="animated-box"></div>
</body>
</html>
```

### Explanation:

- **Keyframes**: The `@keyframes resize` rule defines the animation steps. The element starts at its original size (`scale(1)`), grows to 1.5 times its size at 25%, returns to original size at 50%, grows to double its size at 75%, and returns to original size at 100%.

- **Animation Properties**:
  - `animation-name: resize;` specifies the name of the keyframe animation.
  - `animation-duration: 4s;` sets the duration of one cycle of the animation to 4 seconds.
  - `animation-timing-function: ease-in-out;` provides a smooth transition between the keyframes.
  - `animation-iteration-count: infinite;` makes the animation repeat indefinitely.

You can adjust the scale values, durations, and timing functions to suit your needs.
